PARIS Brazil's Neymar arrived in Paris on Friday following his world record transfer from Barcelona to Paris Saint-Germain, airport officials told AFP. The superstar forward, who moved for 222 million euros ($264m, Sh26.4 billion), arrived at Le Bourget airport and was seen leaving a private jet and getting into a car which joined a motorcade heading towards the city centre, the sources said. He is due to be presented at a press conference at the Parc des Princes at 1130 GMT.   United have splashed the cash this summer.